  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Lifesaving nutrition response&#x2013; SAM treatment and IYCF counselling</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this project is to provide life-saving nutrition services to children suffering severe acute malnutrition (SAM) in the 19 targeted districts across 7 states of Sudan. UNICEF and partners will use CERF for SAM screening and outpatient treatment through therapeutic feeding, as well as skilled counselling services to promote appropriate infant and young child feeding. An estimated 113,188 people including 30,261 SAM children and 82,927 women will benefit from this project, which will be implemented within six months.</narrative>
  </description>
